Package org.semanticweb.vlog4j.core.model.api

Interface Literal

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Entity, SyntaxObject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Fact, NegativeLiteral, PositiveLiteral
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLiteralImpl, FactImpl, NegativeLiteralImpl, PositiveLiteralImpl
    public interface Literal
extends SyntaxObject, Entity
    Interface for literals. A positive literal is simply an atomic formula, i.e., a formula of the form P(t1,...,tn) where P is a Predicate of arity n and t1,...,tn are Terms. A negative literal is a negated atomic formula.
    Author:
    david.carral@tu-dresden.de, Irina Dragoste
